body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

What would you like added/supported?
> I see earlier issues/discussions that $monitor was not even supported. I see it now works and with some look in V3Assert I see Verilator replaces $mointor with always_comb. But this poses a problem as we get prints on every timestamp (sort of explainable given the always_comb). Just wondering if it is easy enough to fix this (Will need to filter out the sensitivity list and knock-off $time).

For sake of completeness, below is LRM ref:

> When a $monitor task is invoked with one or more arguments, the simulator sets up a mechanism whereby
each time a variable or an expression in the argument list changes value—with the exception of the $time,
$stime, or $realtime system functions—the entire argument list is displayed at the end of the time step as

Can you attach an example that runs on other simulators?  (Must be openly licensed, ideally in test_regress format.)
```verilog
module m;

  bit clk, a, b;

  always #10 clk = ~clk;

  initial begin
    $monitor ("%t a: %b b: %b", $time, a, b);
    #100;
    a = 1;
    #10;
    b = 1;
    #10;
    a = 0;
    #10;
    b = 0;
    #100;
    #10;
    $finish (2);
  end
endmodule : m
```

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

> Yes please
